SIMPLE: forging
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Forging
<hw>For"ging</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act
of shaping metal by hammering or pressing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The act of counterfeiting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Mach.)</fld> <def>A piece of forged work in metal;
-- a general name for a piece of hammered iron or steel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There are very few yards in the world at which such
<qex>forgings</qex> could be turned out.</q> <rj><qau>London
Times.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forgivable</ent>⟦br⟧
